            <p>Dear M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Allen&#44; begs&#44; I will<lb/> answer your few lines of enquiry&#44;<lb/> as he is in great trouble about<lb/> his dear Mother who is very ill.<lb/> She was very much better from<lb/> a severe illness last week but had<lb/> a relapse this morning and is<lb/> now very weak &#38; causes all great<lb/> anxiety. Poor M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Levison&#91;&#63;&#93; is<lb/> just alive &#38; his death momen&#45;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>tarily expected he has not been<lb/> <sic>concious</sic> for some days &#38; M<hi rend="sup">r</hi><lb/> Allen has not been able to see<lb/> him  he was unable to receive<lb/> any friends.<lb/></p>
            <p>Regretting  I have to<lb/> write you such a sad letter<lb/> &#38; trusting it may at least<lb/> find you &#38; yours in health<lb/></p>
            <p>I remain yours<lb/>
                Very truly<lb/>
                Rosalie H. Allen<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Tuesday Evening<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
